I think there must be new owners. The Pot Stickers were huge. The Egg Rolls were huge. Didn't give the extra sauce I asked for the Pot Stickers. The Hawaiin Chicken was not wrapped like the menu said. Pieces of Chicken and Ham seprate. Very few pieces of green pepper and tomatoes. While the food is good, Moy Lee has the highest delivery fee around!. $4.00 plus a conveniece fee of $1.50. Tax is between 1.75 % and 1.84%  Not sure if I want to continue ordering from Moy Lee. Have been loyal customers for 15 years.

I met Edmund lee when his family came to Chicago in the 50s and we went to Beaubien school. Moy lee's original restaurant was on Milwaukee Av. by Gale st. I grew up on his Chicken chow mein. Many years later Edmund retired and sold the business. The flavors are a little different but what is missing is consistancy. I hope he can survive in these covid times.

The Oriental Express was also good, but too many pea pods, and they’re bitter(I think naturally) but I LOVE the mushroom variety in it! Excited to try other items! Good stuff. Probably the best Chinese food around. I like the eggs rolls and shrimp with lobster sauce. The egg rolls are humongous, a lot bigger than I remember. I used to come here as a kid. Little greasy but so good. I haven’t been here in a while and just stopped in today. They give big portions and don’t skimp. The veggie fried rice is very good a lot of veggies in it unlike other places. I love that they don’t add a ton of those red pepper flakes all over. All the other regular Chinese food places just pour that on every dish it’s annoying and their meat is good here and doesn’t look like mystery meat like most Chinese food places. Thank you, don’t change anything.

The price is also very affordable. We usually dine in but they have a very busy carry out business. Street parking is free on Milwaukee Avenue.  Super comfortable, no pretension delicious food.

First time trying this long standing spot out...the gentleman at the front was very helpful and very kind... I ordered egg rolls, orange chicken, white rice and chicken fried rice... I will say that the egg rolls were quite good, but very oily... The orange chicken, which is all white meat, to me the best way to go, was good , but a little bit heavy on the sauce...white rice was fine and the chicken fried rice was decent as well... Nothing in particular stands out about the place, but it's been there long time so many people most liked it... If I were in the area again I'd try it out, but maybe something different on their menu, but not a place that I would go out of my way for...

Which would be fine but when we call terrible customer service , The new owners behave as if we are lying we went back with receipt same day we don't live that close got our money back was treated really bad and let them know we will never be in there again .it's just the point if you made a mistake and put it in somebody else's bag don't treat us as if we are the bad guys be nice refund us learn good customer service and you will always keep your recipients!!
